name: KINTON RAMEN ROBSON
review_text:
My first experience with Kinton, a national chain, was back on March 31st when I had what stands to this day as the best Ramen I've ever had.  Unfortunately for me, it was a seasonal feature. Fingers crossed it comes back next year and I will salivate in the mean time. It was the Burnt Shoyu Ramen.

In June of this year, I decided that I deserved more Ramen and made a weekly routine to go for Ramen on my Friday.  Since then, I have returned weekly (missed 1 week cuz vacation). I've endeavored to try a different one every week. I've had the Pork, Chicken, and Beef Original. I've tried the Pork Miso, the Spicy Garlic Chicken (garlic on the side), and the seasonal Chilled Tsukemen. I went with the Spicy Garlic on my second last visit because I kept seeing others order it and was curios why it was seemingly popular. It was the first time I didn't finish the broth as it was too spicy for me. Still very tasty. All have been great, but the Beef Original I had on my most recent visit is definitely my new favorite and I fear I will just have it as a go to and stop trying new items. Variety is the spice (no pun intended) of life!

As for the staff, extremely kind, friendly, efficient, respectful, attentive and competent!  Keep up the excellent work!

Value for your bucks?  By far the best in this category! Plus, they have a stamp card, if you ask, which will get you perks. Win Win!

Can't wait for my next visit!

name: KINTON RAMEN ROBSON
review_text:
7-7-24

Excellent ramen and among the best I can remember having.

Vibrant interior, small, with maybe 8 tables. Seats are hard but not uncomfortable. They are small, however, and if we had to pick on something, this would be it. We aren't big people, and we could see how this might be a problem for larger folks. Also tables seemed a tad crammed together. Service here is fantastic and quick.

We got the following:

Meal for two (39.99 Canadian): This comes with two ramen,  an order of pork/veggie Gyozas (4), and two drinks. We got Beef Miso and Beef Spicy Garlic for our ramen. Both are hearty with noodles. Excellent broth, and the spicy broth has some good heat. Both reorders. The Gyoza (pork) was so good that we ordered another round. Slight crisp outside and scrumptious interior. Comes with a sweet sauce, good, but these are excellent in themselves. We got their homemade lemonade as drinks. Pulp throughout and not overly sweet as you may get elsewhere. Good version.

Meal for one (22.99 Canadian): Comes with one ramen, an order of pork/veggie Gyoza (4), and a drink. Did Chicken Original as the ramen here. Not overly salty broth with a hearty amount of noodles and stuff. Good version.

The Spicy Garlic Beef ramen and the pork Gyoza stick out to us as clear favorites.

You get chopsticks, and your ramen comes with the large ladle/spoon that is typical.

We thoroughly enjoyed our meal
owner_answer: Hi Rick! Thank you for the fantastic review and for sharing your experience with us. We're glad to hear that you enjoyed our ramen and overall dining experience. We appreciate your feedback about the seating and table arrangements, and we will definitely take that into consideration for future improvements. We hope to have the opportunity to welcome you back any time you are in the area :)

We appreciate your feedback and will address this with our team to make sure it doesn‚Äôt happen again. We hope you‚Äôll give us another chance to provide the service and experience you deserve.

name: KINTON RAMEN ROBSON
review_text:
Overall, it‚Äôs a solid place for getting authentic Japanese food. If you come during the summer, I recommend the combo with original broth ramen + gyozas + a drink for only $15.99.

SERVICE: Pretty good. The servers were kind.

ATMOSPHERE: It is a pretty small and closed in restaurant. Bonus points for there being an open kitchen, so you can see the chefs make your dish.

FOOD: Great! I ordered the original broth with pork and gyozas (the gyoza, original broth ramen, and a drink was a really good deal - only $15.99). My friend ordered the Pork Spicy Garlic. The gyozas were nice and crispy, and the filling was good too. The original broth ramen was also delicious, and the portion size is pretty good. The Pork Spicy Garlic ramen was incredibly flavorful, and the noodles were chewy.

name: KINTON RAMEN ROBSON
review_text:
Tried the Beef Original and Meal for One set today. Overall, both noodle bowls had rich and flavourful broth. The Beef Original had a nice balance of beef and pepper ‚Äì the pepper added depth without overpowering the beef. The noodles were cooked perfectly, showing the chef‚Äôs attention to detail. The beef was tender and juicy, with the fat melting in your mouth. The chicken, on the other hand, was chicken breast, so it was expectedly a bit dry and chewy. Still, the meal was definitely worth coming back for.

The only odd part was the service.

1. I started eating around 1:30 p.m., and there were still three empty tables. As soon as I finished one item, the server immediately came to take away the bowl ‚Äì it felt a bit rushed.

2. I was sitting at the bar, and a staff member was seated next to me. After she closed her laptop rather loudly, I glanced over. Unexpectedly, she gave me a sharp, unfriendly glare. Since I was sitting quite close to the kitchen, I felt a little uneasy and didn‚Äôt dare to look again.

Great food overall, but the service made the experience a bit uncomfortable.

The thin noodles were perfectly cooked and held the flavor well, and the pork was tender and full of umami. The atmosphere was cozy and the service was quick and friendly. If you're craving a hearty, spicy bowl of ramen, this place is definitely worth a visit!

name: KINTON RAMEN ROBSON
review_text:
Great ramen if you need to get a snack in the middle of the night and you are not in the mood for pizza, burgers, donair etc.

The prices is reasonable for dinner for 2 for $41.99 plus 2 drinks and choice between gyoza (pork or veggie) or Tokyo Fries.

Gyoza is good. Nice and tangy sauce. Perfect bite and filling is seasoned well.

I ordered pork spicy garlic ramen with thick noodles. Noodles was really good as it has that nice chewy texture and you can slurp the noodles up. The soup is really good with the garlic (freshly grated). Hearty soup has the perfect amount of spicy kick.

I like the soup so much that I drank all of it. This is the 2nd place that I drank the entire soup. The 1st place is at a Vietnamese restaurant in Edmonton.

Highly recommend this ramen place if you are in the mood for a snack in the middle of the night.

name: KINTON RAMEN ROBSON
review_text:
The spicy garlic pork ramen here is one of the best ramens in the city. Complex, perfectly balanced, rich. Actually spicy.

A handful of things ruffled my feathers:
-portion was about 15% smaller than most ramen places
-i get salty when ramen costs more than $20. i get that post-pandemic vancouver demands these prices, especially on this part of robson street.
-it‚Äôs repugnant and deplorable when businesses offer discounts or freebies for 5-star ratings on google. Totally undermines the rating system and makes it useless. It‚Äôs a double shame, because they genuinely have 5-star food.
-in the year 2025, they have a physical stamp card, and it only gets you gyoza after 10 ramens.

Danbo remains undefeated.

name: KINTON RAMEN ROBSON
review_text:
This restaurant gives free ice cream when you review, hence why there are so many positive reviews.

Report the restaurant for giving incentives as follows: go to "Edit" then "Report Business Conduct".

Broth was disappointing and bland. Noodles were well cooked. Toppings were okay but nothing special. Music was so loud that my chair shook the whole time. Overall would not come back. Other ramen joints like Ramen Danbo are more worth the money.
owner_answer:
Hi Sarah, thank you for sharing your feedback with us. We truly appreciate honest reviews, as they help us continuously improve. We want to clarify that we don‚Äôt ask or require customers to leave positive reviews in exchange for anything‚Äîwe simply offer the ice cream as a small thank you for sharing your thoughts, no matter what they may be.

We‚Äôre really sorry to hear that the broth didn‚Äôt meet your expectations, and we‚Äôll definitely take your comments into consideration to improve. We also appreciate your feedback on the music and atmosphere. We want everyone to enjoy their experience comfortably, so we‚Äôll look into adjusting the volume.

We hope you‚Äôll consider giving us another try in the future, and we genuinely appreciate you taking the time to share your experience with us!

name: KINTON RAMEN ROBSON
review_text:
I went to Kinton Ramen Robson on March 29th for their special promotion dinner. I was deeply moved by the restaurant‚Äôs principles, delicious food, and attentive service. There was a long line outside, and a woman in front of me let two friends (a man and a woman) cut in line to join her. Shortly after, two more men arrived, making it a total of four people cutting in. I and the customers behind me expressed our dissatisfaction. The male server consulted the manager and then informed the group that their behavior was not acceptable, leading them to leave.

Near the end of my meal, the same male server who resolved the issue asked me what flavor of cheesecake I would like. Only when I was almost done with my dessert did I realize‚Äîit was a complimentary treat from the restaurant to make up for the earlier unpleasantness! Both the ramen and the cake were incredibly delicious, and the cream that came with the cake was a healthy type that melts smoothly! The restaurant was full of Japanese spirit, with an energetic and orderly atmosphere. Everything was clean, fast, and well-organized, leaving me with a great impression and deep respect. This is definitely the best ramen shop in Greater Vancouver!
